2009.assessment:
Institutions partially recovered from the 2008 crisis. State of emergency lifted;
some political prisoners released. However, executive domination of courts and
legislature persisted. The system returned to competitive authoritarianism baseline.

2007.assessment:
Status unchanged from prior years. Armenia proper under full government control;
Nagorno-Karabakh and surrounding districts under Armenian/NKR control. The Madrid
Principles were put forward by OSCE mediators as a framework but no agreement reached.

2006.assessment:
WJP data not available for Armenia in 2006. Legal transparency remained limited;
government information not systematically published; laws sometimes applied
selectively under oligarchic political system.
